SOLCAT appears to be the third coin released as part of the growing Solamb ecosystem, which has seen several animal-themed Solana meme coins released in recent weeks.
With price action in an ongoing test with localized resistance, SOLCAT is currently trading at a market price of $200 (representing a 24-hour change of 10,277%).
This comes after SOLCAT launched at 15:00PM (UTC) on March 20, in a DEX launch that saw almost immediate traction.

An initial +231% move in the opening hour caught the attention of eagle-eyed DEX traders over the subsequent hours, with price action launching a further +175% after SOLCAT established a lower support zone between $142 and $187.
SOLCAT hit an all-time high at $425 around 19:00 amid influxes of more than $1.12m in trading volume.
However, with early entrants sitting atop more than a +10,000% gain, a localized sell-off triggered retracement moves, which have so far seen SOLCAT tumble -67%.
Yet, all is not over yet, as well-defended consolidation down at lower support above $142 throughout the early hours has now set the stage for a potential second rally leg.
Indeed, with a market cap still sat relatively low at $197k, it seems likely that SOLCAT could undertake an easy 10x move from here in line with other low cap Solana meme coins.
